  "time_ut": 1657284716,
  "original_lang": "si",
  "original_title": "\u0da2\u0db1\u0d9a\u0d9c\u0dda \u0db4\u0dca\u200d\u0dbb\u0d9a\u0dcf\u0dc1\u0dba \u0d9c\u0dd0\u0db1 \u0d9a\u0ddd\u0db4\u0dca  \u0dc0\u0dd2\u0db8\u0dbb\u0dca\u0dc1\u0db1\u0dba\u0d9a\u0dca",
  "text_idx": {
    "en": {
      "title": "A cop inquiry into Janaka's statement",
      "author": "unknown",
      "body_lines": [
        "The Parliamentary Committee on Public Enterprises (COPE Committee) has decided to convene all relevant parties and conduct a comprehensive investigation regarding the controversial statement made by the Chairman of the Public Utilities Commission Mr. Janaka Rathnayake that a liter of petrol and diesel can be given to the people for 250 rupees.",
        "Thus, the Chairman of the Public Utilities Commission, the Minister of Power and Energy Mr. Kanchana Wijesekera, the heads of the Ministry and the Heads of the Petroleum Statutory Corporation",
        "Mr. Charita Herath, the chairman of the committee, said that he will be called before the COP committee on the 12th.",
        "The professor also mentioned that since the statement made by Mr. Janaka Ratnayake is highly controversial, it is essential to conduct further investigations from the people's point of view to find out whether it is true or not.",
        "Meanwhile, Power and Energy Minister Mr. Kanchana Wijesekera posted a note on his Twitter account and requested the Chairman of the Parliamentary Committee on Public Enterprises Professor Charitha Herath to conduct further investigations and reveal the truth to the public regarding the statement made by the Chairman of the Public Utilities Commission.",
        "The Minister further requested that he, the Petroleum Statutory Corporation, the Chairman of the Public Utilities Commission be called and conduct an investigation into this matter.",
        "To inquire about the performance of the Public Utilities Commission, the Chairman of the Commission, Mr. Janaka Ratnayake, and its heads were called before the Parliamentary Committee on Public Enterprises on the 6th. The chairman made the controversial statement in that meeting."
      ],
